<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="545">
<subfield code="a">
Ken Lindsay (1923-2001) was a founding partner of the Challenge Jazz Club in London, England, and worked for the International Bookshop, London, at the time of this correspondence.
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
<subfield code="a">
Collection consists of correspondence between Woody Guthrie and Ken Lindsay in 1952 and 1953, with a few letters from Marjorie Mazia Guthrie and Anneke Van Kirk. Includes four leaves with Guthrie's lyrics for the songs, "Hard travelin'," "Un Americans," "Sunny sun sun," and "Love says no." There are drawings on several of Woody Guthrie's and Anneke's letters to Lindsay.
</subfield>
</datafield>
